## Phase 0 — Parse arguments, resolve PostHog credentials

Read the invocation for `--days` (default 30), optional `--user <email>`, and
the run-mode flags: `--improve` (interactive fix loop, off by default),
`--auto`, and `--auto-fix` (the unattended modes, off by default).

The PostHog Setup block above resolves `PH_KEY`. Confirm it is set. Capture the
window, project, and mode flags:

```bash
DAYS="${ARG_DAYS:-30}"
POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.posthog.com
# Mode flags (1 when the corresponding flag is present, else 0):
#   IMPROVE  ← --improve   (interactive fix loop)
#   AUTO     ← --auto      (unattended; replaces 7a/7c gates with fail-closed guards)
#   AUTOFIX  ← --auto-fix  (unattended build path; IMPLIES --auto)
# --auto-fix implies --auto; --auto (with or without --auto-fix) implies the fix
# loop runs, so IMPROVE is forced on:
[ "${AUTOFIX:-0}" = 1 ] && AUTO=1
[ "${AUTO:-0}" = 1 ] && IMPROVE=1
NONINTERACTIVE="${AUTO:-0}"
echo "window: last ${DAYS}d  ·  user filter: ${ARG_USER:-<all>}  ·  improve: ${IMPROVE:-0}  ·  auto: ${AUTO:-0}  ·  auto-fix: ${AUTOFIX:-0}"
```

`--improve` / `--auto` / `--auto-fix` do NOT change Phases 1–6 — the analysis +
archive run identically. They only activate Phase 7 (the fix loop) AFTER the
report is complete and archived. A run with none of them is read-only as always.

**Unattended modes (`--auto` / `--auto-fix`) — no human is present.** The two
Phase 7 `AskUserQuestion` gates (7a pick-finding, 7c approve-plan) are REPLACED
by fail-closed guard rails: they auto-select the single top P1/P2 finding and
proceed to a build ONLY when the read-only plan clears every guard, otherwise
they STOP with no PR (the analysis + archived investigation prompt is the
deliverable). `--auto` alone never opens a PR; `--auto-fix` is the only flag
that lets an unattended run reach the build path. Never call `AskUserQuestion`
when `NONINTERACTIVE=1`.

**Phase 0 Gate — emit this block before Phase 1:**

```
PHASE 0 GATE
════════════════════════════════
[✓/✗] PH_KEY: present
[✓/✗] Window: last ___ days
[✓/✗] User filter: ___ (or <all>)
[✓/✗] Improve mode: ON / OFF
[✓/✗] Auto mode: OFF / AUTO (no PR) / AUTO-FIX (guarded build) — NONINTERACTIVE=__
════════════════════════════════
GATE: PASS / FAIL — [explain any failures]
```

If GATE is FAIL: stop. Do not query without a key or a window.

